<paragraph id="8BEA0C41FFE0A45FFF5BBE64FE6C6790" blockId="1.[151,1437,1197,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFF5BBE64FEE66704" bold="true" box="[199,322,1377,1404]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Most similar, in size and wing shape to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5577C2FFE0A45FFC81BE67FC206703" box="[797,900,1377,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamna">
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFC81BE67FC206703" box="[797,900,1377,1404]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">A. lamna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5577C2FFE0A45FFC23BE64FB486703" authority="Pyrcz &amp; Gutiérrez &amp; Florczyk, 2019" authorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Gutiérrez &amp; Florczyk" authorityYear="2019" box="[959,1260,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrostriata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFC23BE64FB486703" box="[959,1260,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Argyrophorus rubrostriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2126D28FFE0A45FFB6ABE67FA926704" box="[1270,1334,1378,1404]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFB6ABE67FA946704" bold="true" box="[1270,1328,1378,1404]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but immediately recognized by all silver hindwing dorsal surface, in this respect only similar to the Chilean 
<taxonomicName id="4C5577C2FFE0A45FFA93BE83FEAE67BB" authority="Blanchard" authorityName="Blanchard" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus">
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFA93BE83FA8467D8" box="[1295,1312,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFAB3BE83FA3867E7" box="[1327,1436,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">argenteus</emphasis>
Blanchard
</taxonomicName>
; on turn, the reddish overcast of the forewing ventral surface, in the latter respect most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5577C2FFE0A45FFACFBEAFFE26679F" authority="Pyrcz &amp; Gutiérrez &amp; Florczyk, 2019" authorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Gutiérrez &amp; Florczyk" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argyrophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrostriata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFACFBEAFFE26679F" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Argyrophorus rubrostriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2126D28FFE0A45FFE15BECBFE6C6790" box="[393,456,1486,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B921D053FFE0A45FFE15BECBFE646790" bold="true" box="[393,448,1486,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
